<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 8. Male genitalia of Adriaphaenops petrimaris sp. n. (a) and similarly looking A. kevser (b) (illustrations by Fedor Ciampor)." , "Figure 9. Female genitalia; gonocoxite 1 and 2 (basal and apical segments of gonostylus) of Adriaphaenops petrimaris sp. n. (a), A. rumijaensis (b), and A. kevser (c) (illustrations by Fedor Ciampor)." , "Figure 2. Geographical distribution of the Dinaric aphaenopsoid trechines of the genera Derossiella and Adriaphenops. Source of data: http: // subbio. net / db /" , "Figure 6. Adriaphaenops petrimaris sp. n. in its natural habitat in Pistet 4 cave, Velji Pistet, Kameno more, Risan." , "Figure 7. Habitus of morphologically similar Adriaphaenops species. Adriaphaenops petrimaris sp. n. (a), Adriaphaenops rumijaensis (b) and Adriaphenops kevser (c). Chetotaxy is presented as white points (photo courtesy of Dusan Beno)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/258014" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/258015" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/258009" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/258016" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/258013" .

